Optimizing and Comparing Kernel Types of Support Vector Machines

set.seed(1)
##Generating mock data of 1000 data points and 2 predictor variables
x1 <- runif(1000) - 0.5
x2 <- runif(1000) - 0.5
y <- 1 * (5*x1^4 - 2*x1^3 - 2*x2^3 > 0) #y variable is 1's and 0's
mock <- data.frame(x1 = x1, x2=x2, y=as.factor(y))

#Separating training set (80%) and test set (20%) from mock data
train <- sample(1:length(x1), round(length(x1)*0.8,0)) #Taking 80% of data points as training
test <- (-train) #Remaining points are test
mock_train <- mock[train,] #Divide total dataset into training and test using new indices
mock_test <- mock[test,]
#Create new variable distinguishing which data are assigned to train vs test
mock$train_pt <- if_else(rownames(mock) %in% rownames(mock_train), "train","test")

#Plot to visualize the boundary and confirm data was split into test vs training randomly
mock_colors <- c("0" = "red4", "1" = "dodgerblue3")
ggplot(data=mock, mapping=aes(x=x1, y=x2)) + geom_point(mapping=aes(color=y, shape=train_pt), size=1.5) + scale_color_manual(values = mock_colors) + labs(color="Y-Label", shape="Training vs \nTest Assignment", title = "Mock Categorical Dataset")

Mock data: Linear Kernel, creating optimal model

tic() #Measuring how long it takes for model tune and train on data
mock_linear_tune = tune(svm, y ~ ., data = mock_train, kernel = "linear", #Creating SVM
    ranges = list(cost = c(0.001, 0.01, 0.1, 1, 5, 10)), decision.values=T ) #Tuning for cost, only parameter for linear kernel
toc()
## 0.45 sec elapsed
mock_linear_tune$best.parameters #Printing best parameter values
##   cost
## 3  0.1
mock_linear_tune$best.model #To get number of support vectors
## 
## Call:

##

## [1] 0.125
#Determining test misclassification error
paste0("The linear SVM test prediction table:")
## [1] "The linear SVM test prediction table:"
lin_pred <- predict(mock_linear_tune$best.model, newdata = mock_test)
sum(mock_test$y!=lin_pred)/nrow(mock_test)
## [1] 0.085

table(lin_pred, mock_test$y)

plot(mock_linear_tune$best.model, mock_test)

NHIS Data Preparation

##Loading in data
nhis <- read.csv("C:/Users/danas/Documents/SeattleU/Classes/DATA5322/nhis_2022.csv")

##Select only variables of interest and drop na
nhis_clean <- nhis %>% drop_na %>% select(c("HEARTATTEV", "SEX", "AGE", "HRSLEEP", "BMICALC", "VIG10DMIN"))

#Clean HEARTATTEV variable; Keep only yes (2) and No (1) entries and change to 0=No 1=Yes
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(HEARTATTEV %in% c(1,2)) %>% mutate(HEARTATTEV = if_else(HEARTATTEV == 1,0,1)) %>% mutate(HEARTATTEV = as.factor(HEARTATTEV))

#Clean SEX variable; Keep only Female (2) and Male (1) entries and change to 0=Female 1=Male
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(SEX %in% c(1,2)) %>% mutate(SEX = if_else(SEX == 2,0,1)) %>% mutate(SEX = as.factor(SEX))

#Clean AGE variable; Remove entries that have codes corresponding to unknown responses instead of actual age
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(AGE < 900)

#Clean BMICALC variable; Remove entries that have codes corresponding to unknown responses instead of actual age
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(BMICALC < 900)

#Clean HRSLEEP variable; Remove entries that have codes corresponding to unknown number of hours
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(HRSLEEP <= 25) %>% #entry of 25 means less than one hour
  filter(HRSLEEP > 0) %>% #Entry of 0 means unknown
  mutate(HRSLEEP = if_else(HRSLEEP==25,0,HRSLEEP)) #Round entries of less than one hour down to 0

#Clean HRSLEEP variable; Remove entries that have codes corresponding to inexact values
nhis_clean <- nhis_clean %>% filter(VIG10DMIN < 900) %>% #Entries over 900 are codes not minutes
  filter(VIG10DMIN > 0) #Entry of 0 means unknown
dim(nhis_clean) #Have 8828 entries remaining between 6 variables
## [1] 8828    6
length(nhis_clean$HEARTATTEV[nhis_clean$HEARTATTEV == 1]) #Only 142 entries with heart attack variable

length(nhis_clean$HEARTATTEV[nhis_clean$SEX == 1]) #115 heart attacks with men

## [1] 4728
